\f2\b 3. Predicting Fingers\

\f3\b0 In this scenario I am trying to determine which finger a little girl will land on when she counts on her fingers to 10, 100, and 1000 in a predetermined pattern.\
\
It\'92s challenging to decipher which finger she will land on because the pattern is uncommon and seems inconsistent at first glance. My goal is to determine which finger she\'92ll land on when counting to each number without having to write out the numbers and their corresponding fingers all the way to 1000. To do this, I must find a common theme in the pattern. I would write out the numbers and corresponding fingers just enough to identify a common theme in where the numbers land. \
\
